Does anyone know a way to pre-populate a page template with a custom module?
Looking at the boilerplate theme you can add <@UFTV17Q03> pathâ€™ed modules but when I try to do it with a custom module nothing appears.
```{% block body %}
    {% dnd_area "homepage-hero" label="Homepage Hero" %}
    {% dnd_column width=12 %}    
      {% dnd_module 'homepage-hero' path="../../modules/video-hero" label='Homepage Video Hero' %}{% end_dnd_module %}
    {% end_dnd_column %}
  {% end_dnd_area %}
{% endblock body %}```

For anyone struggling with the above ^ it works when I nest it like this:
```  {% dnd_area "homepage-hero" label="Homepage Hero" %}
    {% dnd_section %}
      {% dnd_column width=12 %}
        {% dnd_row %}        
          {% dnd_module 'homepage-hero' path="../modules/video-hero" label='Homepage Video Hero' %}{% end_dnd_module %}
        {% end_dnd_row %}  
      {% end_dnd_column %}
    {% end_dnd_section %}
  {% end_dnd_area %}```
